intro.title: Introduction to Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics
intro.description: Welcome to the Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics book. This comprehensive guide covers the development of intelligent humanoid robots using ROS 2 and AI agents.

module-1-ros2/chapters/chapter-5-ai-inte.description: This chapter explains how to connect AI agents to ROS 2 to bridge high-level planning with low-level robot control. We'll build a FastAPI server that serves as an interface between AI agents (like OpenAI's GPT models) and ROS 2 systems.

module-1-ros2/chapters/urdf-visualizatio.description: This document explains how to test and validate the humanoid robot URDF model in RViz2.

module-1-ros2/chapters/workspace-setup-g.description: This guide provides detailed instructions for setting up a ROS 2 workspace for humanoid robotics development, with screenshots and verification steps.

module-1-ros2/index.title: Module 1: The Robotic Nervous System (ROS 2)
module-1-ros2/index.description: Welcome to Module 1 of the Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics book. This module covers the fundamentals of ROS 2 as the "nervous system" of humanoid robots, focusing on middleware for robot control.
